# Jikan Cloudflare Worker Proxy Migration Plan

We will redirect all outbound Jikan requests from the Node.js backend through our newly implemented Cloudflare Worker proxy to circumvent Cloudflare/Jikan IP blocks on Render subnets.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration Updates

#### [MODIFY] [constants.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/config/constants.ts)
- Replace `BASE_URL: "https://api.jikan.moe/v4"` with `BASE_URL: "https://animorg-proxy.itisnexora.workers.dev/v4"`.

---

### Diagnostic Endpoints

#### [MODIFY] [server.ts](file:///m:/NEXORA%20GEN/AnimOrg2/backend/src/server.ts)
- Replace the legacy `api.jikan.moe` URLs within the `/debug/jikan` and `/debug/network` endpoints with the Cloudflare Worker URL:
  - `https://api.jikan.moe/v4/anime/21/full` -> `https://animorg-proxy.itisnexora.workers.dev/v4/anime/21/full`
  - `https://api.jikan.moe/v4/random/anime` -> `https://animorg-proxy.itisnexora.workers.dev/v4/random/anime`

